It’s been a journey! I’ve struggled w/ my body image for years. Throwing parties & being a ‘socialite’ in Miami always had me questioning if I was pretty or skinny enough. It’s not until my 30s that I’ve become aware & realized the whole time those small daily changes, “annoying mantras” and cliche quotes of advice are actually 10000% true. 

Consistency IS KING. 🗓️
You NEED A PLAN. 📝
Your environment dictates your MIND. 🌇
It’s a LIFESTYLE not a QUICK FIX! 💣
Be kind to your self. 🫂

Yes, I’ve lost weight and toned up. But it wasn’t until I actually dedicated myself to MYSELF that I got any kind of results. It’s more then just a run or a salad. 😤

I have so much more to share but I’m just getting comfortable sharing my journey in wellness & self-love. Hope I can help motivate someone out there struggling the same way I was to just keep PUSHING! This is a lifestyle - it’s not going to happen over night! 

Have a great day 😚❤️

Share this with a friend who is struggling to see results! Progress, not perfection !! 💪🏾

DO YOU LIKE WHO YOU SEE IN THE MIRROR? 🫂🥲 my wellness journey is ongoing (and is far from over! I’m still figuring it out!) as I’ve tried everything at my disposal to deal with my body image. From the newest fad gym, workout guides, boot camps, meal plans & trainers - I spent so much $ and time looking for a quick fix to taking “care of myself” & didn’t realize the solution was more profound than the physical. 

My body, soul, and mentality weren’t in a suitable space. Everything needed to be re-evaluated. 

The simple truth is - If you want to see results, whether that’s losing weight or loving what you see in the mirror —- you have to make the decision and dedicate yourself to bettering yourself, no exceptions. You can keep running, doing boot camps & eating salads - until you sit and be honest with your diet, your lifestyle & your habits, you won’t be able to move to the next stage of your glow-up. 

WHAT I DID THIS PAST YEAR FOR MY WEIGHT LOSS:

✅ I set a plan for my health & strategized realistic STRENGTH work outs that I could keep up with! (i got a trainer and had him give me homework for days I didn’t see him!)
✅ I ate MORE FOOD! Yes, I ate more food - real food and now eat more then my body weight in grams of protein. I also eat every 3 hours! I use apps to track my calories and to help me remember to eat! 
✅ I walk 10k Steps a day!! Drink water! 
✅Cut down drinking dramatically 
✅ Changed my social environment to adapt for less stress and chaos ☺️ can’t stress this enough! 

It starts with you. You are the priority. Ruthlessly & selfishly. I know that when I wake up now, I choose me everyday. And it feels so damn good. You should try it! ❤️

#weightlossjourney #miamifitness #glowuptips #miamilife #latinablogger #miamiinfluencer #somiami #miaminightlife #miamilifestyle
